
// This Hyperlambda code sends a signal using the [sockets.signal] slot to a session specified by the expression [x:@.session]. It transmits an argument [args] containing a [function_error] node, which holds the value of the [message] node from the [.arguments] node. This setup is typically used for notifying a session about an error message.
sockets.signal:x:@.session
   args
      function_error:x:@.arguments/*/message
